WEBVTT

00:01.502 --> 00:03.837
♪♪

00:03.837 --> 00:05.589
Darling,
you're still in your pajamas.

00:05.589 --> 00:07.132
Here, let's get you dressed.
Dylan: Don't.

00:07.132 --> 00:08.800
JJ wants to be
more independent.

00:08.800 --> 00:10.677
He wants to
unbutton his own shirt today.

00:10.677 --> 00:12.679
I tried to do it,
and he bit my hand.

00:12.679 --> 00:13.805
JJ...

00:13.805 --> 00:15.349
that's very resourceful.

00:15.349 --> 00:16.558
All right, darling,
you let me know

00:16.558 --> 00:18.310
when and if
you need my help.

00:18.310 --> 00:19.728
"Never."
What?

00:19.728 --> 00:22.356
"Can you just watch
without..."

00:22.356 --> 00:24.525
H‐E ‐‐
"helping at all?"

00:24.525 --> 00:27.194
Are you kidding?
I can do absolutely nothing...

00:27.194 --> 00:28.612
for as long as it takes.

00:28.612 --> 00:30.822
[ The New Pornographers'
"Dancehall Domine" plays ]

00:30.822 --> 00:32.699
♪ Ooh, oh, oh, ooh ♪

00:32.699 --> 00:34.826
♪ Oh‐oh‐oh ♪

00:34.826 --> 00:36.703
♪ Ooh, oh, oh, ooh ♪

00:36.703 --> 00:37.955
♪ Oh‐oh‐oh ♪

00:37.955 --> 00:39.790
♪ They love you
with the lights on ♪

00:39.790 --> 00:41.583
♪ Repeat it, recite it ♪

00:41.583 --> 00:43.335
♪ Whenever you feel gentle ♪

00:43.335 --> 00:45.337
♪ Whenever you'll be knighted ♪

00:45.337 --> 00:47.130
♪ Some will have
to brave the line ♪

00:47.130 --> 00:49.091
♪ But they're letting you
right in ♪

00:50.759 --> 00:52.594
♪ They love you
with the lights on ♪

00:52.594 --> 00:54.596
♪ Turn them on or don't bother ♪

00:54.596 --> 00:56.014
♪ Never been so loved ♪

00:56.014 --> 00:58.225
♪ But you're handling it well,
lover ♪

00:58.225 --> 00:59.893
♪ Just like every idea ♪

00:59.893 --> 01:02.104
♪ Was to be like no other ♪

01:03.772 --> 01:07.359
♪ What we call
the dancehall domine ♪

01:07.359 --> 01:09.778
♪ Embedded, indebted,
don't let it ♪

01:09.778 --> 01:11.363
♪ No, never let it be said ♪

01:11.363 --> 01:13.115
♪ I've got, got the floor ♪

01:15.284 --> 01:18.662
♪ In the heart,
in the heart, in the heart ♪

01:20.622 --> 01:22.291
Look at you.

01:22.291 --> 01:23.667
Already dressed for bed.

01:25.043 --> 01:27.045
You're ahead of the game,
love.

01:30.799 --> 01:34.845
♪♪

01:34.845 --> 01:37.681
Oh! Oh, Ms. DiMeo!
Thank you for coming.

01:37.681 --> 01:39.766
You're probably wondering
why I asked you here.

01:39.766 --> 01:41.018
You did?

01:41.018 --> 01:42.352
I just came
to take some pens.

01:42.352 --> 01:44.938
Oh, what a happy coincidence!
[ Chuckles ]

01:44.938 --> 01:46.648
Please, sit.

01:46.648 --> 01:48.817
Um...
I‐I wanted to discuss

01:48.817 --> 01:51.361
the timing
of Kenneth's summer hiatus.

01:51.361 --> 01:52.487
What summer hiatus?

01:52.487 --> 01:53.780
Well, once school is out,

01:53.780 --> 01:56.074
the district won't pay
for his services.

01:56.074 --> 01:58.493
I'm afraid that
you'll have to do without him.

01:59.703 --> 02:01.538
Really?

02:01.538 --> 02:03.248
What, like all summer?
I mean, he doesn't ‐‐

02:03.248 --> 02:04.791
he doesn't come back during July
or something?

02:04.791 --> 02:06.251
He does not.
Oh, my God!

02:06.251 --> 02:08.086
So I get my JJ back
all summer!

02:08.086 --> 02:09.379
Ooh, I could kiss you,

02:09.379 --> 02:11.882
you nervous little bird
of a woman!

02:11.882 --> 02:13.634
Come here! Come on.

02:13.634 --> 02:16.011
[ Laughing ]

02:16.011 --> 02:18.138
Oh, they warned me
about the crazy.

02:18.138 --> 02:19.931
No one prepared me
for your heart.

02:20.849 --> 02:23.894
♪♪

02:28.023 --> 02:30.067
What are you doing
to our air?

02:30.067 --> 02:31.526
Modern dance.

02:31.526 --> 02:34.446
I'm telling a story
with my body.

02:34.446 --> 02:36.490
I've never felt
so supple and expressive.

02:36.490 --> 02:37.574
Cool.

02:37.574 --> 02:38.742
Where would you like me
to punch you?

02:38.742 --> 02:40.661
My arm.

02:40.661 --> 02:42.579
My gym grade is
dragging down my GPA,

02:42.579 --> 02:46.041
so I'm doing Honors Modern Dance
as my Phys. Ed. requirement.

02:46.041 --> 02:48.502
Ray, I've done
a pretty good job so far

02:48.502 --> 02:50.420
of staying out
of your shame radius,

02:50.420 --> 02:52.673
but the splash zone on this one
is just too big.

02:52.673 --> 02:54.758
You're gonna bring me down
with you.

02:54.758 --> 02:56.968
Let me teach you how to run
so you can stay in gym.

02:56.968 --> 02:58.804
Thanks, Dylan.

02:58.804 --> 03:01.765
You easily could've filmed that
and used it to embarrass me.

03:01.765 --> 03:03.600
I'm glad you decided
to help me instead.

03:06.061 --> 03:08.188
I played this totally wrong.

03:09.481 --> 03:10.482
Oh! Darling,
you look nice.

03:10.482 --> 03:12.067
Oh!

03:12.067 --> 03:13.610
Tucked in shirt?
[ Chuckles ]

03:13.610 --> 03:15.320
What's with the trying?
There's no trying.

03:15.320 --> 03:17.948
I'm stuck having dinner
with a dad I barely know

03:17.948 --> 03:19.825
because our wives thought
we might like each other.

03:19.825 --> 03:21.410
Oh, darling, don't judge.

03:21.410 --> 03:23.161
Maybe you'll like Dane.

03:23.161 --> 03:25.247
You know his wife, Sarah.
She's lovely.

03:25.247 --> 03:26.706
Yeah,
and if he's anything like her,

03:26.706 --> 03:28.834
he'll be dull as dirt
with a...

03:28.834 --> 03:31.420
kind‐of nice butt.

03:31.420 --> 03:32.587
Okay, then.

03:32.587 --> 03:34.631
Uh...JJ, Kenneth,

03:34.631 --> 03:36.216
there's something
we need to discuss.

03:36.216 --> 03:37.634
Please have a seat.

03:37.634 --> 03:39.136
What's wrong?

03:39.136 --> 03:41.972
You, Kenneth my friend ‐‐
You're going away...

03:41.972 --> 03:44.182
for the whole summer!
[ Laughs ]

03:44.182 --> 03:45.183
I was aware.

03:45.183 --> 03:46.309
Kenneth:
You're taking it well.

03:46.309 --> 03:47.853
I can't believe it,
actually.

03:47.853 --> 03:51.064
In two weeks time,
it's the return of the May‐Jay.

03:51.064 --> 03:52.941
May‐Jay?
Our summer nickname.

03:52.941 --> 03:54.901
And we're gonna need it for
all our mother/son adventures.

03:54.901 --> 03:56.111
Where are May‐Jay?

03:56.111 --> 03:58.655
Oh, they're at the beach
on a bike with a sidecar.

03:58.655 --> 04:02.075
What's that cool thing
May‐Jay are wearing?

04:02.075 --> 04:03.535
Matching hats!

04:03.535 --> 04:04.536
Oh!

04:07.747 --> 04:08.832
[ Laughs ]

04:08.832 --> 04:10.584
You don't have
a more recent picture?

04:10.584 --> 04:13.253
All right, two weeks, pal.
Get it out now.

04:13.253 --> 04:15.088
Dude,
when are you gonna tell her

04:15.088 --> 04:17.132
you want to go to camp
all summer?

04:17.132 --> 04:18.008
[ Sighs ]

04:18.008 --> 04:20.510
"There's never a good time,

04:20.510 --> 04:23.638
and she's so thirsty
for summer."

04:23.638 --> 04:25.974
[ Sighs ] Well,
you're running out of time.

04:25.974 --> 04:27.809
But good use of "thirsty."

04:27.809 --> 04:28.727
So, what are you
gonna say?

04:28.727 --> 04:30.479
"No idea.

04:30.479 --> 04:32.522
What do you think
she'll buy?"

04:32.522 --> 04:35.066
Yeah...
I don't know, buddy.

04:35.066 --> 04:36.568
We're getting
into a weird area.

04:36.568 --> 04:39.070
There's some things that an aide
is supposed to do,

04:39.070 --> 04:43.200
but providing tips
on how to manipulate moms ‐‐

04:43.200 --> 04:44.659
that's definitely not
on the list.

04:47.287 --> 04:49.372
But, you know,
on an unrelated note,

04:49.372 --> 04:52.083
I have this friend ‐‐
J. I.

04:52.083 --> 04:56.463
Yeah, well, J. I.,
he wants to go to <i>winter</i> camp.

04:56.463 --> 04:57.881
But his mom, <i>Paya,</i>

04:57.881 --> 04:59.508
won't let him go.

04:59.508 --> 05:04.012
I think he should
use Paya's vanity against her,

05:04.012 --> 05:07.516
make it seem like going to camp
shows what a good mom she is.

05:07.516 --> 05:08.975
[ Chuckles ]

05:08.975 --> 05:10.435
That's just a story about

05:10.435 --> 05:13.480
my good friend <i>J. I.</i>
and <i>Paya.</i>

05:15.398 --> 05:17.275
It's clear I'm talking about y‐‐
Yeah, okay.

05:20.570 --> 05:21.738
We're fully booked tonight.

05:21.738 --> 05:23.156
I'm sorry.
I don't think we can seat you.

05:23.156 --> 05:24.866
Oh, that actually works out
'cause I don't want to be here.

05:24.866 --> 05:26.326
Jimmy!
Hey!

05:26.326 --> 05:27.410
Oh, Mr. Richmond!

05:27.410 --> 05:29.120
I didn't realize he was
with <i>you.</i>

05:29.120 --> 05:30.038
Right this way.

05:30.038 --> 05:32.833
Thank you, Tina.

05:32.833 --> 05:34.459
Tony!

05:34.459 --> 05:35.502
That's Tony.

05:35.502 --> 05:37.504
He is the worst guy.

05:37.504 --> 05:39.256
Let's see
what we're dealing with.

05:39.256 --> 05:41.174
We'll just run
around the block.

05:41.174 --> 05:42.217
Should I get some
of that black stuff

05:42.217 --> 05:44.302
that sports people
put under their eyes?

05:44.302 --> 05:46.012
Maybe once
you're a sports person.

05:46.012 --> 05:48.223
♪♪

05:48.223 --> 05:49.474
Hey, let's
throw down some apps.

05:49.474 --> 05:51.059
Jimmy,
what looks good to you?

05:51.059 --> 05:53.144
How spicy is
the eggplant dish?

05:53.144 --> 05:55.313
Archie, get my man here
an eggplant.

05:55.313 --> 05:57.148
No spice ‐‐
He's got a delicate palette.

05:57.148 --> 05:58.692
No, actually, I like spicy.

05:58.692 --> 06:00.902
Archie, bring him
the spiciest eggplant

06:00.902 --> 06:02.487
anyone has ever seen.

06:02.487 --> 06:04.906
I want people to die
making this eggplant.

06:04.906 --> 06:05.615
Archie: You got it, Dane.

06:05.615 --> 06:06.616
Anything else?

06:06.616 --> 06:08.201
Nah.
Jimmy, come on.

06:08.201 --> 06:10.078
Uh...
It's your night, baby!

06:10.078 --> 06:11.913
Does the band take
requests?

06:11.913 --> 06:13.665
For my Jimmy,
yes, they do.

06:13.665 --> 06:16.626
[ Playing "Blitzkrieg Bop" ]

06:16.626 --> 06:18.086
[ Giggling ]

06:18.086 --> 06:19.963
What is going on here?

06:19.963 --> 06:21.590
How are you so connected?

06:21.590 --> 06:24.175
I got a little juice here,
I'm not gonna lie.

06:24.175 --> 06:26.595
It's all about being
a regular

06:26.595 --> 06:27.971
and knowing the right people.

06:27.971 --> 06:30.432
Cool! Very cool!

06:30.432 --> 06:32.601
Dane noticed you eyeing
the other table's soufflé,

06:32.601 --> 06:34.978
so he had me bring <i>you</i>
the last one.

06:36.354 --> 06:39.024
[ High‐pitched ] Dane?!

06:39.024 --> 06:40.442
♪♪

06:40.442 --> 06:41.902
Nice!

06:41.902 --> 06:44.237
This is a good pace
for a beginner like you.

06:44.237 --> 06:47.782
Now let's slowly ease up
to top speed.

06:47.782 --> 06:48.992
Wh‐Wh‐What the ‐‐

06:48.992 --> 06:52.037
♪♪

06:54.789 --> 06:57.083
[ Breathing heavily ]
That was fun.

06:57.083 --> 06:59.711
So, uh...
how hard were you trying?

06:59.711 --> 07:00.879
Wait a minute.

07:00.879 --> 07:02.756
You were trying your hardest,
weren't you?

07:02.756 --> 07:03.757
[ Panting ]

07:03.757 --> 07:05.091
Oh, my God!

07:05.091 --> 07:06.676
I'm the fastest runner
in the family.

07:06.676 --> 07:08.762
I beat you, Dylan.

07:08.762 --> 07:11.097
I'm a sports person!

07:13.058 --> 07:14.851
It was amazing, Maya.

07:14.851 --> 07:17.270
The flatbreads flowed
like wine.

07:17.270 --> 07:19.230
At a certain point,
I was like, "Aah!

07:19.230 --> 07:20.899
Enough with the flatbreads!
We still have entrées coming!

07:20.899 --> 07:22.442
And Dane,
he laughed at that.

07:22.442 --> 07:23.610
Wow.

07:23.610 --> 07:24.986
I haven't seen you
this giddy

07:24.986 --> 07:26.863
since someone mistook you
for their state assemblyman.

07:26.863 --> 07:28.406
I just like Dane.

07:28.406 --> 07:30.659
I told him next time we go out,
I'd return the favor.

07:30.659 --> 07:32.118
How?

07:32.118 --> 07:33.495
You don't get special treatment
anywhere.

07:33.495 --> 07:35.747
A‐Are you suggesting
I don't have juice?

07:35.747 --> 07:37.666
I ‐‐ I have juice.
Where?

07:37.666 --> 07:40.835
Oh! The Carl's Jr.,
where you eat for free

07:40.835 --> 07:42.045
'cause you got beaten up
in the parking lot.

07:42.045 --> 07:44.297
I have juice
in other places.

07:44.297 --> 07:46.841
No, y‐y‐you have no juice,
darling.

07:46.841 --> 07:48.259
[ Laughing ]
You're juiceless.

07:48.259 --> 07:50.470
Okay, <i>I</i> do have juice,

07:50.470 --> 07:52.972
and <i>you</i> could take a note or two
from Dane

07:52.972 --> 07:55.433
on how to make a man
feel good.

07:57.936 --> 07:59.521
[ Alarm beeps ]

07:59.521 --> 08:01.481
♪♪

08:01.481 --> 08:02.691
Morning, Ray!
Have a good sleep?

08:02.691 --> 08:03.692
Good.
Want to go for a race?

08:03.692 --> 08:05.110
Ready, set, go.

08:05.110 --> 08:06.319
Is this because I beat you?

08:06.319 --> 08:09.364
It was a fluke,
and I demand a rematch.

08:09.364 --> 08:11.282
Why would I give you
a rematch?

08:11.282 --> 08:13.243
I've never lost a race.

08:13.243 --> 08:15.578
I'm retiring
at the top of my game.

08:15.578 --> 08:17.247
Let's see.

08:17.247 --> 08:20.166
What do sports champions do
after they hang it up?

08:20.166 --> 08:22.460
Oh, God,
they lose everything!

08:22.460 --> 08:23.545
Oh, wait.

08:23.545 --> 08:25.213
George Foreman
turned out okay.

08:25.213 --> 08:26.423
I'll just invent
something.

08:26.423 --> 08:28.007
Ray...

08:28.007 --> 08:30.009
running fast is my thing.

08:30.009 --> 08:32.262
If you take this from me,

08:32.262 --> 08:35.640
I can assure you,
you will regret it.

08:35.640 --> 08:39.185
You also assured me
that you were the fastest DiMeo.

08:39.185 --> 08:40.854
And...

08:40.854 --> 08:42.439
that turned out wrong.

08:42.439 --> 08:45.692
Ooh, Sports Ray has
some sass to him!

08:48.319 --> 08:51.823
"The summer my mom
taught me to.."

08:51.823 --> 08:53.491
F‐I‐‐ "fish."

08:53.491 --> 08:54.534
[ Voice breaking ]
I remember that.

08:56.745 --> 08:59.789
"The summer my mom
taught me to"...

08:59.789 --> 09:02.667
F‐L‐‐ "fly a kite."

09:02.667 --> 09:04.294
Darling, it's so lovely.

09:04.294 --> 09:06.755
I mean, I know Mother's Day
isn't for a few days.

09:06.755 --> 09:08.214
Is this my gift?

09:08.214 --> 09:09.174
No? Good.

09:09.174 --> 09:11.009
'Cause you know
I love my brunch.

09:11.009 --> 09:12.761
I'd really like to have
both things.

09:12.761 --> 09:15.263
Aww, empty.

09:15.263 --> 09:17.390
What will fill it?
It's poetic.

09:17.390 --> 09:19.350
You get that from me.
[ Chuckles ]

09:19.350 --> 09:20.852
So, what do you want to do?

09:20.852 --> 09:23.021
[ Sighs ]

09:23.021 --> 09:27.692
"I'd like to go to camp."

09:27.692 --> 09:28.985
Oh, they have those,
do they?

09:28.985 --> 09:30.153
Mother/son camps?

09:37.160 --> 09:40.038
Looks a bit light
on the mothers.

09:40.038 --> 09:41.372
10 weeks?

09:41.372 --> 09:43.875
No, wait.
I don't understand.

09:43.875 --> 09:45.794
Summer's going to be our time.

09:45.794 --> 09:47.003
It always has been.

09:47.003 --> 09:48.379
What's changed?

09:48.379 --> 09:50.924
"What changed is me,

09:50.924 --> 09:56.137
thanks to the greatest mother
in the world."

09:56.137 --> 09:59.140
"Your..." L‐O‐V‐E ‐‐
"love gave me the..."

09:59.140 --> 10:02.102
S‐T ‐‐ "strength
to spread my wings."

10:02.102 --> 10:03.436
Oh, that's what changed,
is it?

10:03.436 --> 10:07.565
"And it is on the wings
of your love

10:07.565 --> 10:09.442
that I will soar."

10:09.442 --> 10:10.318
[ Chuckles ]

10:13.863 --> 10:15.115
Paya looks mad, J.I.

10:19.327 --> 10:20.703
Where do you get the nerve
helping my son manipulate me?

10:20.703 --> 10:23.331
"I asked Kenneth
to help me.

10:23.331 --> 10:27.127
"I really want to go
to..." C‐‐ "camp."

10:27.127 --> 10:29.212
It's why I've been
working on my..."

10:29.212 --> 10:31.172
B‐U‐T‐T ‐‐ "butt."

10:32.632 --> 10:34.175
Button, button.

10:34.175 --> 10:35.552
It's our summer.

10:35.552 --> 10:37.178
I mean, what?

10:37.178 --> 10:39.514
Am I supposed to just spend it
with someone else?

10:39.514 --> 10:40.765
May‐Ray?

10:40.765 --> 10:42.392
That just sounds
so stupid.

10:42.392 --> 10:44.602
You can't just spring this
on me, darling.

10:44.602 --> 10:46.688
10 weeks is too long
away from home,

10:46.688 --> 10:47.814
and I'm ‐‐ I'm sorry,

10:47.814 --> 10:49.232
but I just don't think
you're ready.

10:49.232 --> 10:51.401
Maya,
you are wrong on this one.

10:51.401 --> 10:52.735
Are you still here?

10:52.735 --> 10:54.904
'Cause this is between
me and my son, okay?

10:54.904 --> 10:56.447
No.
Excuse me?

10:56.447 --> 10:58.032
He wants to push himself.

10:58.032 --> 10:59.367
And I know you want
to protect him,

10:59.367 --> 11:01.286
but you need
to get out of his way.

11:01.286 --> 11:03.246
And I think I see this
more clearly than you.

11:03.246 --> 11:04.581
He's going.

11:04.581 --> 11:07.250
♪♪

11:07.250 --> 11:09.043
Two pieces of good news ‐‐

11:09.043 --> 11:11.087
one, your summer
starts now.

11:11.087 --> 11:12.255
Farewell.

11:12.255 --> 11:13.631
And two...

11:13.631 --> 11:15.466
I'll give you a little bit
of a head start.

11:15.466 --> 11:16.676
Before what?

11:16.676 --> 11:19.679
Ten, nine...

11:19.679 --> 11:20.763
three...

11:20.763 --> 11:22.307
Okay, bye.

11:22.307 --> 11:23.641
[ School bell rings ]

11:23.641 --> 11:24.684
Hello, Raymond.

11:24.684 --> 11:25.977
Hello?

11:25.977 --> 11:27.562
How 'bout those
seven new planets

11:27.562 --> 11:30.106
they discovered
in the TRAPPIST‐1 galaxy?

11:30.106 --> 11:31.274
What?

11:31.274 --> 11:32.233
How do you know
about that?

11:32.233 --> 11:33.568
I'm smart now.

11:33.568 --> 11:35.570
I'm taking your identity.

11:35.570 --> 11:38.198
But I could give it back...
for a rematch.

11:38.198 --> 11:39.324
Mm.

11:39.324 --> 11:40.575
All because I beat you.

11:40.575 --> 11:43.244
Beet ‐‐ a red vegetable
eaten by weirdoes.

11:43.244 --> 11:45.205
Like looking in a mirror,
ain't it?

11:45.205 --> 11:46.831
I'm not racing you again.

11:46.831 --> 11:48.708
Oh, I'll get my rematch!

11:48.708 --> 11:50.084
What?

11:50.084 --> 11:52.003
At whom are you looking?

11:52.003 --> 11:54.380
[ Groans ]
I hate being smart.

11:56.591 --> 11:57.592
What is it?

11:59.219 --> 12:00.345
JJ...

12:00.345 --> 12:01.679
Oh, darling,
I get the point.

12:01.679 --> 12:03.348
You are capable.

12:03.348 --> 12:05.141
But we can't do another
button day yet, love.

12:05.141 --> 12:07.602
It's too soon.

12:07.602 --> 12:10.188
I know Kenneth is filling
your mind with big ideas,

12:10.188 --> 12:11.564
but I do know you better.

12:11.564 --> 12:13.066
And that camp looks lovely,

12:13.066 --> 12:15.693
but you've never spent
a single night away from home.

12:15.693 --> 12:17.779
Easy, JJ.

12:17.779 --> 12:20.657
"Don't blame Kenneth
for something I want to do."

12:20.657 --> 12:22.992
Oh, come on, JJ.

12:22.992 --> 12:24.994
As if I would ever
do that.

12:24.994 --> 12:26.579
[ Thud ]
[ Gasps ] Are you okay?

12:28.915 --> 12:30.333
Thanks a lot, Kenneth!

12:31.626 --> 12:33.336
How are you doing,
my brave man?

12:33.336 --> 12:34.379
Good.
"Good."

12:34.379 --> 12:36.297
Right, you meant JJ.
That makes sense.

12:36.297 --> 12:38.132
We made it here in record time,
didn't we?

12:38.132 --> 12:39.300
[ Smooches ]
Practice makes perfect.

12:39.300 --> 12:40.718
Right, we'll go and register.
You bring JJ.

12:40.718 --> 12:42.303
On it.

12:42.303 --> 12:43.388
Hey, sorry.

12:43.388 --> 12:44.931
I will move my car
as soon as I can.

12:44.931 --> 12:46.266
No problem, Mr. DiMeo.
We know you here.

12:46.266 --> 12:47.684
We'll keep it in front.
Really?

12:47.684 --> 12:49.060
We'll throw in a wash,
too.

12:49.060 --> 12:51.854
Do I have juice...

12:51.854 --> 12:53.439
at the hospital?

12:53.439 --> 12:54.983
[ Crystals'
"And Then He Kissed Me" plays ]

12:54.983 --> 12:56.609
How you doing?
Hey, Jimmy!

12:56.609 --> 12:57.986
Hey, Loretta!

12:57.986 --> 12:59.112
Hey, you don't have
to wait out here.

12:59.112 --> 13:00.613
Right this way.

13:00.613 --> 13:03.449
Man: You see that?! They
just took him straight back.

13:03.449 --> 13:05.076
Hey, guys!
Jimmy's back!

13:05.076 --> 13:06.202
Orderly: Jimmy DiMeo?

13:06.202 --> 13:07.662
‐Hey, Jimmy.
‐Hey, Jimmy!

13:07.662 --> 13:08.871
Jimmy: Hey, guys!

13:08.871 --> 13:11.374
There's the crew!
Looking sharp!

13:11.374 --> 13:12.625
What's good Jimmy?!
How are you, man?

13:12.625 --> 13:13.793
Kids are good?

13:13.793 --> 13:15.211
Nurse:
Oh, my God! Hey, Jimmy!

13:15.211 --> 13:16.963
Every time, you two.
Don't you work?!

13:16.963 --> 13:18.673
‐Jimmy!
‐Hey, Jimmy!

13:18.673 --> 13:20.174
‐Hey, Jimmy!
‐Jimmy!
‐Uh‐oh!

13:20.174 --> 13:22.051
Jimmy: What's up!

13:22.051 --> 13:23.720
Come on,
we're gonna take a shortcut.

13:23.720 --> 13:25.847
[ Woman groaning ]

13:25.847 --> 13:27.515
Uh...it's a boy.

13:27.515 --> 13:28.641
Hey, good eye, Jimbo!

13:28.641 --> 13:30.435
♪ ... wait to see him again ♪

13:30.435 --> 13:31.978
Loretta, you're the best.
Right there.

13:31.978 --> 13:33.730
DiMeo's in the house!

13:33.730 --> 13:34.897
Hey, Jimmy!

13:34.897 --> 13:37.525
Jimmy!

13:37.525 --> 13:38.860
Nurse: Jimmy!

13:38.860 --> 13:39.861
Doctors.

13:39.861 --> 13:41.779
All: Hi, Jimmy!

13:41.779 --> 13:43.072
Nurse #2:
Jimmy, where are you going?
Come back here.

13:43.072 --> 13:44.866
‐Jimmy! Nice to see you.
‐Hey, Jimmy!

13:44.866 --> 13:46.701
Unh‐unh! Aah!
[ Chuckles ]

13:46.701 --> 13:48.870
Hey, Lucy, is 222 open?
It is now.

13:48.870 --> 13:50.329
Kick that amputee
out of 222!

13:50.329 --> 13:53.332
♪ And then he kissed me ♪

13:53.332 --> 13:54.584
Anything you need, Jimmy,
just let me know.

13:54.584 --> 13:57.253
♪ And then he kissed me ♪
Mr. DiMeo!

13:57.253 --> 13:58.337
♪ And then he kissed me ♪

13:58.337 --> 13:59.797
Something to drink,
Mr. DiMeo?

13:59.797 --> 14:01.924
Juice.

14:04.052 --> 14:05.845
Dylan:
You see that tree?

14:05.845 --> 14:07.513
Who do you think
could make it out there faster?

14:07.513 --> 14:08.765
You.

14:08.765 --> 14:10.349
But we ain't gonna
find out.

14:10.349 --> 14:11.893
JJ, buddy!

14:11.893 --> 14:13.811
Thank God!
When I heard...

14:13.811 --> 14:15.438
[ Laughs nervously ]

14:15.438 --> 14:17.190
You look good.

14:17.190 --> 14:18.816
Real ‐‐ real good.

14:18.816 --> 14:19.734
[ Exhales sharply ]

14:19.734 --> 14:21.944
[ Sighs ] Rookie.

14:21.944 --> 14:26.407
I'm sorry. You look so ‐‐
so small and so washed out.

14:26.407 --> 14:27.867
And the wires ‐‐
What's with the wires?

14:27.867 --> 14:29.535
[ Voice breaking ]
What did they hook him up to?!

14:29.535 --> 14:31.829
They control the television,
Kenneth.

14:31.829 --> 14:33.748
JJ's gonna be just fine.

14:33.748 --> 14:35.833
He dislocated his kneecap.

14:35.833 --> 14:38.002
We're just waiting to see
if he's gonna need surgery.

14:38.002 --> 14:40.129
He had the same procedure done
on his other knee

14:40.129 --> 14:41.047
a few years ago.

14:41.047 --> 14:42.090
[ Knocking ]
Oh, kids?

14:42.090 --> 14:45.176
Do you want
to grab a soda?

14:45.176 --> 14:47.053
How you holding up, JJ?

14:47.053 --> 14:48.513
Let's take a look.

14:48.513 --> 14:49.722
[ Winces ]

14:49.722 --> 14:51.557
You're killing him!
Get away!

14:51.557 --> 14:52.809
Jimmy: Okay.
All right, Kenneth.

14:52.809 --> 14:54.977
Thank you so much.
You're a rock.

14:57.146 --> 15:00.066
So, we are gonna have to perform
a lateral release.

15:00.066 --> 15:01.901
I'll talk to the surgeons.

15:01.901 --> 15:02.985
You know the drill.

15:02.985 --> 15:04.612
You're gonna do great.

15:04.612 --> 15:05.571
♪♪

15:05.571 --> 15:07.198
Oh, darling.

15:07.198 --> 15:08.908
It's all right.

15:10.118 --> 15:12.203
"Forget"...
C‐A‐‐ "camp.

15:12.203 --> 15:13.871
You were right.

15:13.871 --> 15:15.498
I can't do it."

15:15.498 --> 15:17.542
Darling,
we'll talk about it later.

15:17.542 --> 15:18.668
Just...

15:18.668 --> 15:20.753
You rest now.

15:20.753 --> 15:22.880
"No, it's fine.

15:22.880 --> 15:25.466
I can't undo a button

15:25.466 --> 15:28.469
without putting myself
in the hospital."

15:29.637 --> 15:32.390
Hey, hey, hey.

15:32.390 --> 15:34.809
I am connected here.

15:34.809 --> 15:36.060
Do you want
to name a baby?

15:39.605 --> 15:41.065
♪♪

15:41.065 --> 15:43.025
I am so sorry.
I didn't get it.

15:43.025 --> 15:44.318
Don't send him to camp.

15:44.318 --> 15:45.570
Protect that child!

15:45.570 --> 15:47.113
Lock him away.

15:47.113 --> 15:49.073
I judge you
for letting me near him!

15:49.073 --> 15:50.867
You don't know me!
Who am I?

15:50.867 --> 15:53.411
Some groundskeeper
you met off the street?

15:53.411 --> 15:54.996
Yeah, I need you
to talk to JJ.

15:54.996 --> 15:56.247
Don't make me talk to him!

15:56.247 --> 15:57.331
I'll fall on him!

15:57.331 --> 15:58.457
Get your head on straight,

15:58.457 --> 16:00.042
and explain to him
he is going to camp.

16:00.042 --> 16:01.210
What?

16:01.210 --> 16:03.212
He just told me that
I was right,

16:03.212 --> 16:04.505
he can't do it.

16:04.505 --> 16:06.299
Now, I am not the person

16:06.299 --> 16:07.925
who convinces him
what he cannot do.

16:07.925 --> 16:09.051
So, that's not taken?

16:09.051 --> 16:10.428
I‐I can be that person.

16:10.428 --> 16:13.472
It's his time to soar.
Those are your terrible words.

16:13.472 --> 16:15.349
He used to listen
to everything I said,

16:15.349 --> 16:18.769
but, for whatever reason,
you have that now.

16:18.769 --> 16:20.104
You've come to matter.

16:21.439 --> 16:23.107
Get ready to matter.

16:23.107 --> 16:24.609
♪♪

16:24.609 --> 16:25.943
Wasn't this nice?

16:25.943 --> 16:28.738
I know we're fighting,
but it's important for us

16:28.738 --> 16:31.115
to be here for each other
in times like this.

16:31.115 --> 16:32.783
Yeah,
it's so much more important

16:32.783 --> 16:34.827
than that stupid stuff
about who's faster.

16:34.827 --> 16:35.995
Totally.

16:35.995 --> 16:38.289
And JJ's gonna be fine.

16:38.289 --> 16:40.333
Surgeries like this are
old hat to him.

16:40.333 --> 16:41.709
I know.

16:41.709 --> 16:43.502
And I have to admit,
one thing that I like is

16:43.502 --> 16:45.796
how JJ's always so nice to me
after surgery.

16:45.796 --> 16:47.173
Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

16:47.173 --> 16:48.674
It's a tender moment
between brothers.

16:48.674 --> 16:50.092
The fact that it's aided
by pain killers

16:50.092 --> 16:52.428
only subtracts from it
slightly.

16:52.428 --> 16:54.347
Not sure if you've noticed,
but I'm always sure

16:54.347 --> 16:56.140
that I'm the very first person
that he sees

16:56.140 --> 16:57.475
after he gets out of surgery

16:57.475 --> 16:59.977
so I can hog up
all that sweet JJ love.

16:59.977 --> 17:01.437
I have noticed that.

17:01.437 --> 17:03.814
It's almost like you'd
do anything

17:03.814 --> 17:06.275
to make sure you were
the first person by his side.

17:06.275 --> 17:07.610
What are you getting at?

17:07.610 --> 17:08.819
'Kay, not proud of it,

17:08.819 --> 17:10.655
but I kind of turned
your ringer off.

17:10.655 --> 17:13.699
And JJ kinda went into surgery
and is getting out...

17:13.699 --> 17:15.660
kind of now.
No!

17:15.660 --> 17:17.245
JJ, I'm coming for you!

17:17.245 --> 17:18.996
Let's make it official!
Ready, set, go!

17:24.126 --> 17:25.544
You're good at hurdling,
too?

17:30.007 --> 17:32.009
♪♪

17:34.345 --> 17:35.680
Yes!

17:35.680 --> 17:37.640
[ Breathing heavily ]
You won,

17:37.640 --> 17:40.059
fair and square.

17:40.059 --> 17:41.644
Go ahead.

17:41.644 --> 17:42.853
I deserve it.

17:50.319 --> 17:52.071
You were pretty fast.

17:52.071 --> 17:55.157
Like the sun
revolving around...

17:55.157 --> 17:56.784
whatever.

17:59.537 --> 18:01.455
Hey!

18:01.455 --> 18:03.124
You did great!

18:03.124 --> 18:04.292
[ Chuckles ]

18:04.292 --> 18:06.794
You, uh...
you looking here?

18:06.794 --> 18:09.422
L‐O‐‐ "Love"?

18:09.422 --> 18:10.548
Yeah?

18:10.548 --> 18:12.216
Don't mind if I do.

18:12.216 --> 18:13.134
[ Chuckles ]

18:13.134 --> 18:13.843
Ahh.

18:16.262 --> 18:19.765
Brightening some kid
in the hospital's day.

18:19.765 --> 18:21.851
I really am a star athlete.

18:23.603 --> 18:24.478
[ Knock at door ]

18:30.985 --> 18:32.903
Hey, buddy.

18:32.903 --> 18:35.197
You feeling okay?

18:35.865 --> 18:37.825
So, your mom told me

18:37.825 --> 18:39.493
you decided not to go
to camp.

18:41.537 --> 18:43.247
"It's too much.

18:43.247 --> 18:45.207
I'm not ready."

18:45.207 --> 18:47.793
Oh, yeah, but you were
so excited about going to camp.

18:47.793 --> 18:50.796
What about
challenging yourself?

18:50.796 --> 18:52.632
"Why are you not..."

18:52.632 --> 18:55.092
L‐O‐O‐‐
"looking at me?"

18:55.092 --> 18:56.510
Whaaat?

18:56.510 --> 18:57.887
I gotta be looking at <i>you</i>
all the time?

18:57.887 --> 18:59.305
Like you're so great.

18:59.305 --> 19:01.849
I just happen to be looking
at other things,

19:01.849 --> 19:03.142
like that wall,

19:03.142 --> 19:05.686
or ‐‐ or ‐‐ or
that TV.

19:05.686 --> 19:07.480
Oh, boy.

19:07.480 --> 19:10.107
So many wires
in my little buddy.

19:11.150 --> 19:13.152
[ Clatters ]

19:15.613 --> 19:17.615
Oi!

19:17.615 --> 19:20.242
Oh!

19:20.242 --> 19:21.952
That floor's slippery.
You're gonna...

19:21.952 --> 19:24.538
want to watch
that spot.

19:24.538 --> 19:26.582
[ Door closes ]

19:26.582 --> 19:28.584
Okay, listen.

19:28.584 --> 19:29.835
All that nice stuff that

19:29.835 --> 19:32.171
Kenneth said about me before
as a mum,

19:32.171 --> 19:34.590
I don't know how much of that
came from you,

19:34.590 --> 19:37.343
but it's spot on.

19:37.343 --> 19:38.928
I am good.

19:38.928 --> 19:40.513
I'm damn good.

19:40.513 --> 19:42.014
But it's only because

19:42.014 --> 19:45.184
I am determined to be the mother
that you deserve.

19:45.184 --> 19:47.353
You ‐‐ I know you hate it
when people say this,

19:47.353 --> 19:49.814
but I am not people.

19:49.814 --> 19:51.857
You inspire me, darling.

19:51.857 --> 19:53.567
You always have.

19:53.567 --> 19:56.237
More so now
you're growing up...

19:56.237 --> 19:58.114
taking risks.

19:58.114 --> 19:59.824
Darling...

19:59.824 --> 20:03.285
you will do whatever you want
in your heart.

20:03.285 --> 20:05.579
Your body doesn't get a say.

20:05.579 --> 20:08.290
If you don't want
to go to camp,

20:08.290 --> 20:10.376
I suppose we could have
a fun summer.

20:10.376 --> 20:12.128
I mean, who knows?

20:12.128 --> 20:14.880
I haven't really given it
much thought.

20:14.880 --> 20:18.300
But if you do want to go,
we'll get you ready.

20:18.300 --> 20:19.552
Together.

20:19.552 --> 20:20.720
Believe that.

20:20.720 --> 20:22.513
♪♪

20:22.513 --> 20:24.473
It's been a long day.

20:24.473 --> 20:25.599
Sleep on it.

20:36.402 --> 20:38.404
What? What is it?

20:42.908 --> 20:44.410
Damn right, you're going.

20:47.872 --> 20:48.956
Dane: Whoa!
You can't park here.

20:48.956 --> 20:50.499
Jimmy: It's okay.
They know me.

20:50.499 --> 20:52.752
We're taking a right.
Okay.

20:52.752 --> 20:54.211
No peeking.

20:54.211 --> 20:55.296
I'm not peeking.

20:55.296 --> 20:56.964
And...open!

20:56.964 --> 20:58.257
I know
what you're thinking.

20:58.257 --> 21:00.968
How did I get a room this nice

21:00.968 --> 21:02.511
on such short notice?

21:02.511 --> 21:03.929
I've got some juice.

21:03.929 --> 21:06.056
Normally, these would just be

21:06.056 --> 21:07.850
a gift for a new mother.

21:07.850 --> 21:10.352
Tonight, they're a gift
for my new friend.

21:10.352 --> 21:12.313
So, we're eating steaks
that were intended

21:12.313 --> 21:14.315
for mothers who had
just given birth.

21:14.315 --> 21:16.692
Yeah.
This is...

21:16.692 --> 21:17.777
awesome.

21:17.777 --> 21:19.361
We're losing him.
Get the paddle!

21:19.361 --> 21:21.363
Oh, ho, ho!
Dinner and a show!

21:21.363 --> 21:22.740
Very nice.
Cheers, pal.

21:22.740 --> 21:23.574
Clear!
[ Thud ]
